fun @mlift-elapsed@10106[1,0,1,0] : forall<a,(e :: E)> (t0 : std/time/duration/duration, x : a) -> <(std/core/types/ndet :: X)|(e :: E)> (std/time/duration/duration, a);
// Return the number of fractional seconds that it takes to evaluate `action`.
pub fun elapsed[50,9,50,15] : forall<a,(e :: E)> (action : () -> <(std/core/types/ndet :: X)|(e :: E)> a) -> <(std/core/types/ndet :: X)|(e :: E)> (std/time/duration/duration, a);
// monadic lift
fun @mlift-print-elapsed@10107[1,0,1,0] : forall<a,(e :: E)> (msg : (std/core/types/@optional :: V -> V)<std/core/types/string>, @y-x10102 : (std/time/duration/duration, a)) -> <(std/core/types/ndet :: X),(std/core/console/console :: X)|(e :: E)> a;
// Measure the number of fractional seconds that it takes to evaluate `action`, and print `msg` postfixed with the
// measured time in millisecond resolution.
pub fun print-elapsed[58,9,58,21] : forall<a,(e :: E)> (action : () -> <(std/core/types/ndet :: X),(std/core/console/console :: X)|(e :: E)> a, msg : (std/core/types/@optional :: V -> V)<std/core/types/string>) -> <(std/core/types/ndet :: X),(std/core/console/console :: X)|(e :: E)> a;
 
